# UX-INTERACTION.md — reference only

[`UX-INTERACTION.md`](../../UX-INTERACTION.md) records MaNaReD UX decisions and interaction rationale. It is **not** an implementation backlog.

## Allowed

- **Read** for context when discussing, reviewing, or documenting UX
- **Edit** `UX-INTERACTION.md` when the user asks to update UX rationale or documentation

## Not allowed without explicit user request

- Implementing features described in `UX-INTERACTION.md` (routes, components, filters, PQRS, etc.)
- Modifying `src/app/`, `src/worker.tsx`, README, DESIGN.md, AGENTS.md, or Figma based on doc content or doc edits alone
- Treating status values (`not built`, `TBD`, `Figma TBD`) as tasks to execute automatically

## When editing the UX doc

- Change **only** `UX-INTERACTION.md` unless the user explicitly asks for cross-file updates (e.g. "also link from README")
- Do not "sync" or propagate doc changes into code or other docs proactively

## When implementation is requested

The user must ask explicitly (e.g. "build the filter sidebar", "implement from UX-INTERACTION"). Then follow [`vibework.mdc`](./vibework.mdc), [`ui-stack.mdc`](./ui-stack.mdc), and [`figma-design-system.mdc`](./figma-design-system.mdc) for the actual build.
